            <title>[LU-10001] kernel update [SLES12 SP3 4.4.82-6.6]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10001</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SUSE Linux Enterprise 12 SP3 kernel was updated to receive the following security fixes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2017-1000251: The native Bluetooth stack in the Linux Kernel was&lt;br/&gt;
  vulnerable to a stack overflow while processing L2CAP configuration&lt;br/&gt;
  responses, resulting in a potential remote denial-of-service vulnerability&lt;br/&gt;
  but no remote code execution due to use of CONFIG_CC_STACKPROTECTOR.&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;a href=&quot;#1057389&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;bnc#1057389&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
